The paper focuses on the application of deep learning techniques to the keyword spotting task, which is a subfield of speech recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and residual networks (ResNets), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the use of dilated convolutions, which are a type of convolutional operation commonly used in natural language processing tasks, suggesting that the paper could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to improve accuracy, suggesting that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the development of speech-based interfaces, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
